whereas.text:
Whereas according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (referred to in this preamble as the 
          CDC
        ), nearly 26,000,000 individuals in the United States have diabetes and an estimated 79,000,000 individuals age 20 years or older in the United States have prediabetes;

Whereas a Mathematica Policy Research study found that total expenditures for individuals with diabetes receiving benefits under the Medicare program under 
          title XVIII of the Social Security Act (
          42 U.S.C. 1395 et seq.
        ) in fiscal year 2005 comprised 32.7 percent of the budget for such program in  such fiscal year;
